TestDictLiteralSetsAndNavigates
/ A dict literal binds field-by-field — %u.name% is "a" and %u.age% is 30 after
/ set %u% = {name:"a", age:30}. The Dictionary navigator collapses into the dict
/ value type so navigation hits Get(key) directly.
- set %u% = {name:"a", age:30}
- assert %u.name% equals "a"
- assert %u.age% equals 30
